// The FIRST chunk carries `content_type` populated (e.g. "application/pdf"
// or "application/json") so the proxy can set Content-Type on its HTTP
// response before any bytes flow. Subsequent chunks leave content_type
// empty and carry only `data`. The final chunk may be a zero-length
// `data` — the server closes the stream when the file is fully sent.
